The paper discusses unsupervised or self-supervised neural networks playing minimax games in game-theoretic settings, which is a topic that falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and information theory (cs.IT). Given that the paper focuses on neural networks and their applications in game theory, it is most likely to be classified under cs.LG, followed by cs.AI and cs.CV. However, since the paper also discusses the theoretical aspects of these networks, it could also be classified under cs.NE and cs.IT.
